		<title type="html"><![CDATA[General • Re: Making an Android APK]]></title>

					<category term="General" scheme="http://love2d.org/forums/viewforum.php?f=3" label="General"/>
		
		<content type="html" xml:base="http://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?t=86645&amp;p=252805#p252805"><![CDATA[
You do not need to know how to generate APKs, but as Google Play Store required you to upload AAB packages, APKTool wouldn’t work, as it generates only APK<br><br>First, you need to install appropriate SDK version via Android Studio, then you change some values as game name etc in manifest and put your game source code to some specific folder and hot compile (once you install sdks, you can automate the build with script)<br><br>If you are stuck somewhere or have problem with something, just ask on the forum and someone will help you. Just try it and explain, where you are stuck.<br><br>Also if you manage to compile it, you can make some more begginner friendly instructions and post it here for future users<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=141490">Andlac028</a> — Mon Jan 16, 2023 2:16 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
