I'm new here...as well as rather new to coding in general, but I think that an "RPG editor" is a great idea! I've been working through various tutorials/examples, and for me, an "object oriented" or "modular" approach for the many different components of an RPG, (or any kind of game, really), (such as sound, input, physics, events, states, ai, text/dialogue, inventory, serializing data, particles, shaders, etc.) has been the easiest to understand and organize. I've used RPGmaker in the past, and while I found it to be a great tool for "storyboarding" or "prototyping" an idea, coding something of my own from scratch, or building on what others have provided, has given me much more flexibility and insight.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=212438">zingo</a> — Mon Jan 16, 2023 8:08 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
